 Bellars, Leicestershire, England":"Kirby Bellars, Leicestershire, Anglie","England":"Anglie"},"da":{"1265–after 1288":"1265–efter 1288","1265–1288":"1265–1288","1267–1290":"1267–1290","1285–1335":"1285–1335","1305–1364":"1305–1364","1305–Male":"1305–Afdød","–1303":"–1303","1240–1303":"1240–1303","1246–Female":"1246–Afdød","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1246":"1246","1267":"1267","1288":"1288","1265":"1265","1364":"1364","after 1288":"efter 1288","about 1262":"omkring 1262","about 1285":"omkring 1285","Kettleby, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England","Kirby Bellars, Leicestershire, England":"Kirby Bellars, Leicestershire, England","England":"England"},"nl":{"1265–after 1288":"1265–na 1288","1265–1288":"1265–1288","1267–1290":"1267–1290","1285–1335":"1285–1335","1305–1364":"1305–1364","1305–Male":"1305–Overleden","–1303":"–1303","1240–1303":"1240–1303","1246–Female":"1246–Overleden","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1246":"1246","1267":"1267","1288":"1288","1265":"1265","1364":"1364","after 1288":"na 1288","about 1262":"circa 1262","about 1285":"circa 1285","Kettleby, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England","Kirby Bellars, Leicestershire, England":"Kirby Bellars, Leicestershire, England","England":"England"},"en":{"1265–after 1288":"1265–after 1288","1265–1288":"1265–1288","1267–1290":"1267–1290","1285–1335":"1285–1335","1305–1364":"1305–1364","1305–Male":"1305–Deceased","–1303":"–1303","1240–1303":"1240–1303","1246–Female":"1246–Deceased","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1246":"1246","1267":"1267","1288":"1288","1265":"1265","1364":"1364","after 1288":"after 1288","about 1262":"about 1262","about 1285":"about 1285","Kettleby, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England","Kirby Bellars, Leicestershire, England":"Kirby Bellars, Leicestershire, England","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bellers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Bellars  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bellairs","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire): variant of   Bellars  , suggesting French <i>belle(s) aire(s)</i> ‘lovely demeanor’."]},{"name":"Bellars","meanings":["(2010: NA)","English (Northamptonshire):","(of Norman origin): apparently from Old French <i>bélier</i> ‘ram’, hence a nickname for someone thought to resemble a ram in some way or possibly a metonymic occupational name for a shepherd. In Northamptonshire the name attracts excrescent <i>-s</i> already by 1377."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Violet  ,   Vivien  , or   Vivian ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vivien","meanings":["Earlier generally taken as a variant of the boy's name   Vivian  , but now also rarely used for boys. This spelling was quite common in Old French. Its use as a girl's name in the English-speaking world was influenced by  Tennyson's  Merlin and Vivien (  1859 ). This name, from Arthurian legend, may represent an altered form of a Celtic name (perhaps akin to the Irish Gaelic name <i>Béibhinn</i> ‘white lady’, pronounced ‘bee-<b>veen</b>’). The actress  Vivien Leigh  (  1913–67 ) was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Violet","meanings":["From the name of the flower (Old French <i>violette</i>, Late Latin <i>violetta</i>, a diminutive of <i>viola</i>). This was one of the earliest flower names to become popular in Britain, being used as early as  1700  and becoming well established in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph II Bellers of Eye Kettleby was born in 1265, in Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England, his father, Hamon de Bellers of Kirby, was 25 and his mother, Mabel Mansell, was 20. He had at least 4 sons with Sybbell de Perers. He died after 1288, in Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1265–after 1288":"1265–pärast 1288","1265–1288":"1265–1288","1267–1290":"1267–1290","1285–1335":"1285–1335","1305–1364":"1305–1364","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","–1303":"–1303","1240–1303":"1240–1303","1246–Female":"1246–Surnud","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1246":"1246","1267":"1267","1288":"1288","1265":"1265","1364":"1364","after 1288":"pärast 1288","about 1262":"umbes 1262","about 1285":"umbes 1285","Kettleby, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, Un